      <description>According to the OOW page:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Extra spell slot - For the first time, characters can earn an additional spell slot allowing for even more versatility.&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't *think* I'm breaking the NDA by discussing this, but I've been playing the OOW beta and am familiar with the ninth slot and how it's earned. As a necro, I've discovered that my playstyle is going to go through some changes as I adapt to having an extra spell slot.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My spell lineup for LDONs usually looks something like:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Eduring Darkness (Snare, Magic Dot)&lt;br&gt;Pyrocuror (Fire Dot)&lt;br&gt;Neurotoxin (Poison DD)&lt;br&gt;Mind Wrack (Group mana tap)&lt;br&gt;Touch of Mujaki (Lifetap)&lt;br&gt;Force Shield (Rune)&lt;br&gt;Rune of Death (Pet Haste)&lt;br&gt;Death Peace (Feign Death)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Depending on LDON theme and group makeup, I may change out certain spells for my undead spells. I will also sub in situational, preperation, or buff spells at the appropriate times. I don't keep my pet summons out because I will almost always be FD when my pet dies and can't realy summon another if several LDON mobs are beating on me. Seduction of Saryrn (HP -&gt; Mana) lasts long enough that I usually don't have to cast it more than once per LDON. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With that 9th spell slot coming, I'm sort of at a loss which will be most important to keep memmmed. I can always keep Splurt up. It's a relatively cheap DOT that does great damage on long fights. I can also always keep Sedulous Subversion (Twitch) up for when I'm grouping with non-experienced/lazy/stupid healers. Another serious option will to be to keep up my various pet heals or pet blocks. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Aghg! I'm at a loss. My strategy is about to change and I'm not sure which direction it's going to be changing in.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Assuming that the 9th spell slot is reasonable for everyone to obtain (it is), how will you change your spell line up to take advantage of a new spell slot?</description>
